page.title: 01Henstead & Rushmere
page.content: This region is part of rural Suffolk, situated only 2 km inland from the coastal resort of Kessingland. The river Hundred meanders at no greater height than 2m above sea level through a shallow valley rising to a plateau of 20m above sea level. Rushmere, on the north bank, faces Henstead on the south. Both settlements are small and dispersed with few amenities. Countryside can be said to predominate over people therefore and this fact is reflected throughout the following pages of information.
